import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['precipitation'].plot.hist(bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation (inches)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature (F)')
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    weather_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the most common weather condition observed in Seattle?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
